➜“改天”的英语是 the other day吗？
http://www.sohu.com/a/410768694_100197508	35331
<p class="ql-align-center">“改天请你吃饭”是大家生活中经常可以听到的<strong>客套话。</strong></p>
<p class="ql-align-center"><img src="http://p7.itc.cn/images01/20200731/935afc10cbda466ab85fb49573204cd8.gif" max-width="600" /></p>
<p class="ql-align-center">那么，“改天”应该怎么用英语表达呢？</p>
<p class="ql-align-center">是the other day还是another day呢？</p>
<p class="ql-align-center">今天一起来了解一下有关于day的说法吧！</p>
<p class="ql-align-center"><strong>the other day≠改天</strong></p>
<p class="ql-align-center"><strong>the other day = not long ago</strong></p>
<p class="ql-align-center"><strong>意思是几天前、不久以前</strong></p>
<p class="ql-align-center">The other day, he cut the grass on his lawn.</p>
<p class="ql-align-center">几天前，他才修理完院子里的草坪。</p>
<p class="ql-align-center"><img src="http://p6.itc.cn/images01/20200731/b68c45928dbb4d1387d213409d2b9f4e.jpeg" max-width="600" /></p>
<p class="ql-align-center"><strong>而another day意思是改天、又一天、新的一天</strong></p>
<p class="ql-align-center">如果你今天没空想说<strong>改天</strong></p>
<p class="ql-align-center">就可以说：</p>
<p class="ql-align-center">How about another day？</p>
<p class="ql-align-center">Maybe some other time.</p>
<p class="ql-align-center"><img src="http://p9.itc.cn/images01/20200731/eb9971d230da4d39900a09a0704b350a.jpeg" max-width="600" /></p>
<p class="ql-align-center"><strong>今天几号怎么说？</strong></p>
<p class="ql-align-center"><strong>What's the date today？</strong></p>
<p class="ql-align-center"><strong>今天几号？</strong></p>
<p class="ql-align-center"><strong>注意</strong>：What day is it today？是问今天是周几，day前面是没有the；而What's the date today?是问今天几号，date前面一定要加the哦！</p>
<p class="ql-align-center">What day is it today?</p>
<p class="ql-align-center">今天是星期几？</p>
<p class="ql-align-center">What time is it?</p>
<p class="ql-align-center">现在几点了？</p>
<p class="ql-align-center"><strong>询问月份</strong></p>
<p class="ql-align-center"><strong>What month is this?</strong></p>
<p class="ql-align-center"><strong>It's April.</strong></p>
<p class="ql-align-center">月份：January, February, March, April, May, June,</p>
<p class="ql-align-center">July, August, September, October, November, December</p>